icum Magnum” 609.54. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>abstract</b> an idea or word from its context, τὸ ἀγαθὸς ἀποκοπέν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anonymus “in SE” 57.31. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ἀ. τινὰ ἀπὸ τόπου <b>beat off from</b> a strong place, of soldiers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.4.39, 4.2.10. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, <b>smite the breast in mourning</b>: with <i>accusative</i>, <b>mourn for,</b> νεκρόν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 628.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0609","accentedUnicode":"ἀποκόπτω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G2875","matchingForm":"κόπτω","stepTransliteration":"koptō","gloss":"to cut/mourn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"哀號, 砍下","_es_Gloss":"cortar/lamentar","_zh_Gloss":"哀号, 砍下"}],"shortDef":"to cut off; emasculate","mediumDef":"to cut off; emasculate <br /><b>to cut off,</b> <ref='Mrk.9.43, 45'>Mk. 9:43, 45</ref>; <ref='Jhn.18.10, 26'>Jn. 18:10, 26</ref>; <ref='Act.27.32'>Acts 27:32;</ref> <b>to castrate, to emasculate, make a eunich,</b> <ref='Gal.5.12'>Gal. 5:12</ref>*","stepGloss":"to cut off","stepTransliteration":"apokoptō","count":6,"_es_Definition":"cortar o separar; med. mutilar o castrarse uno mismo","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 切除, 砍斷<br> 1a) 肢體<br> 1b) 非身體之物 (徒 27:32)","_zh_Definition":"1) 切除, 砍断<br> 1a) 肢体<br> 1b) 非身体之物 (徒 27:32)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"chặt; cắt. ἀπό (G575) + κόπτω (G2875)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"削掉","_es_Gloss":"cortar","_zh_Gloss":"削掉"}]}